A 10mm rendition of the famous Bretonnian special character for Warmaster. The Green Knight holds a special place in my heart — I received my Warhammer miniature as a gift from my wife years ago, and it’s been a cherished piece ever since.

This is just a minor edit of the fantastic model of Ilhadiel: https://www.myminifactory.com/object/3d-print-green-knight-miniature-32mm-modular-262486

There are two versions, with or without pennant. I have not printed him yet, hope the detail survives.

Jules is still my favourite Warhammer character, but Bertrand and his merry band is close second (I am a huge Robin Hood fan). Thus I had to convert them to 10mm. This single stand should complement my Bowmen stands nicely.

The poor rabbit Hugo caught is converted from https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/friendly-rabbitfolk-32mm-scale
